{"author":{"id":"4bb6c1767e50694cfde61856db22bf137d1651e8a0b5ca858c486db3dd02f280"},"ops":[{"type":3,"timestamp":1778555073,"nonce":"rBra6axu0p39QrDBzKWtUG22+Nk=","message":"**Finalised matrix design (2026-05-11)** — diverges from the body's original proposal.\n\nAfter design conversation, the sweep is **8 new training cells** (not 4 as originally proposed) and targets `full_trial_pl` (lit__full_nojerk), not `post_go_pl` (lit__post_nojerk), as the cleaner test bed for `--nn-output-pre-go`. The reasoning: `full_trial_pl` has effectively-zero hold-period position penalty (the powerlaw schedule on `effector_hold_pos` makes the hold-period multiplier ≈ 7×10⁻⁴ at end of hold), so the only effective pre-go pressure comes from catch trials, giving the `--nn-output-pre-go` lever a clean independent effect to measure.\n\n**Cells:**\n\n| # | Cell | hold_pos | pos_running | hold_sched | run_sched | nn_output_pre_go |\n|---|---|---|---|---|---|---|\n| 1 | `post_go_pl__pos10` | 10 | 10 | flat | powerlaw | 0 |\n| 2 | `full_trial_pl__pos10` | 10 | 10 | powerlaw | powerlaw | 0 |\n| 3 | `full_trial_pl__prego_1e-3` | 1 | 1 | powerlaw | powerlaw | 1e-3 |\n| 4 | `full_trial_pl__prego_5e-2` | 1 | 1 | powerlaw | powerlaw | 5e-2 |\n| 5 | `full_trial_pl__prego_1` | 1 | 1 | powerlaw | powerlaw | 1.0 |\n| 6 | `full_trial_pl__pos10_prego_1e-3` | 10 | 10 | powerlaw | powerlaw | 1e-3 |\n| 7 | `full_trial_pl__pos10_prego_5e-2` | 10 | 10 | powerlaw | powerlaw | 5e-2 |\n| 8 | `full_trial_pl__pos10_prego_1` | 10 | 10 | powerlaw | powerlaw | 1.0 |\n\n**Two analysis axes:**\n1. **Position-weight scaling (×10)**: Cells 1, 2 — test whether 10× position weight accelerates reach (currently arriving near end of trial). For `post_go_pl__pos10`, the `flat` hold schedule means the hold-period penalty IS meaningful at 10× and should suppress anticipation directly.\n2. **Pre-go output mask sweep (3 weights × 2 pos_scales = 6 cells)**: Cells 3-8 — test whether `--nn-output-pre-go` ∈ {1e-3, 5e-2, 1} suppresses residual anticipation in `full_trial_pl` at both pos=1 and pos=10. The cross gives a preliminary read on whether the pre-go mask and the position-weight scaling are independent levers or interacting ones.\n\n**Existing baselines included in analysis (not retrained):** `lit__post_nojerk` and `lit__full_nojerk` from f47abb1, plotted at the top of every comparison figure.\n\nNaming: dropped `__nojerk` suffix since all cells are no-jerk; renamed `lit__post_nojerk` → `post_go_pl` and `lit__full_nojerk` → `full_trial_pl` for cleaner provenance.\n\nWall clock: ~32 min/cell on RTX 4090 → ~4.3 h sequential for 8 cells.\n\nRun plan artifacts on `feature/3702f54-pregomatrix`.","files":null}]}